features: AMD AM5 Socket: Ready for AMD Ryzen 7000 Series Desktop Processors
Ultrafast Connectivity: PCIe 4.0 support, dual M.2 slots, USB 3.2 Gen 1 ports, front USB 3.2 Gen 1 Type-C
ASUS OptiMem II: Careful routing of traces and vias, plus ground layer optimizations to preserve signal integrity for improved memory overclocking

Two-way AI Noise-Cancelation: Reduces background noise from the microphone and audio output for crystal-clear communication in games or video conferences
ASUS CSM motherboard: ASUS Corporate Stable Model, with up to 36-month Supply, EOL notice & ECN control
ASUS Control Center Express(ACCE) to make IT endpoint management
ASUS Event log for capturing and managing detailed system information
Dedicated LPC header and debug card with LCD display for faster troubleshooting
body.description: The ASUS PRIME A620M-A-CSM commercial motherboard provides enhanced enterprise level features, including comprehensive system protection, 24/7 stability & reliability and an improved management suite ASUS Control Center Express to smooth your IT operations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Was a Gift, so Far it works well. Good for an A620, Actually its the best ive seen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Defective board, that happens. ASUS support site was down for _days_. Never again ASUS.
reviews.reviewText: Flakey board, but almost works. Pretty close to worst case.Crashes after hours of burn-in, sometimes. After removing my video board problem persisted.Eventually I found the board would consistently fail in Windows Memory Diagnostic, but only if you ran the very slow test for hours. Much time was wasted. Not a memory fault, a hardware failure.No bios available for days as the download site was down for 'maintenance'. That was two wasted days. Was just _unacceptable_.This was the last chance I was giving ASUS.Once they made quality hardware.They built a brand.IMHO they've been running their brands into the ground like MTD mowers for 15 years now.No ASUS brands ever again. I've spec machines for work before and likely will again.I really should have dropped them after the last laptop, but laptops are a sideshow.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice board but complicated BIOS
reviews.reviewText: Asus makes nice boards but the BIOS on this one needs work. If you have a long post boot or no video but PC on, you're missing a BIOS update and other settings. Google for longer than 5 min post boot on the board. Once BIOS has all the settings correct it's fast. Check your memory. If it's AMD EXPO set that in the BIOS too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great, solid value.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This board has everything you need for a mid- high end PC at a great value. Bolstering the AM5 socket for the fastest gaming chips, enough clearance to plug everything in even with a massive GPU, 2 fourth gen m.2 ports for lightning fast storage, wifi capabilities if you're into that, fast ethernet, DDR5 ram and so on. Absolute winner of a purchase abs would recommend to anyone who wants a good value AM5 board.

reviews.reviewTitle: Defective out of the box, dont buy ASUS
reviews.reviewText: Weirdest problem ever, I couldnt install windows because it kept freezing in installation. It was a nightmare to find the problem, but it was probably the ram slot of cpu socket. Bought a motherboard from MSI and no problem at all
